Barely four days after Governor Abubarkar Sani Bello assured of adequate security for communities sacked by terrorist groups, one person have been killed while nine others, including two men, seven women and their children have been abducted by armed bandits in Shashai village, Munya Local Government Area of Niger state. This is coming few days after the Governor visited Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) camp in Central Primary School Gwada, Shiroro Local Government, where he also that issues of insecurity will soon be a thing of the past as police are working hard to clear explosives planted in some localities by the criminals.    The latest attack occurred at about 1: am (Tuesday morning) in Kuchi Ward when undisclosed number of armed bandits invaded the sleepy community and killed a farmer who doubles as a local gun fabricator. As the armed bandits opened fire at late, Audu, his neighbour who was trying to escape from the scene also sustained gunshot wound and he is responding to treatment in one of the health facilities in the area, one of the neighbours told our correspondent. The invaders, according to the source entered Shaishai village through one of the bush paths, shot sporadically into the air to scare away possible intruders and headed to the house of late, Audu, said to be helping the local vigilantes in the manufacture of guns they use in fighting the criminals. The armed bandits who were said to have entered Shashai village through foot path, moved from one house after another and abducted two men and seven women with their babies also disappeared through same route. Efforts to confirm the latest attack from the Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), Niger state police command, DSP Wasiu A. Abiodun proved abortive as at the time of this report. Our correspondent called his mobile number but he could not pick.